    "Another potential drawback of a machine learning approach, especially as it involves a deep neural network and SHAP, is the high computational cost of the computation.",
    "For the first part, access to a GPU is imperative, while the second part needs a sufficiently large CPU.",
    "The computational cost produced by SHAP could be decreased by aggregating features (i.e., time points into time windows).",
    "However, the major advantage of EEG analyses over other neuroscientific methods (e.g., fMRI) is their extremely high temporal resolution.",
    "Hence, decreasing the granularity might conflict with the overall goal and benefits of this analysis."
